mcqs.question:
What is the output of the following code?

int x = 10;
if (x > 5)
 System.out.println("A");
System.out.println("B");

What is the output of this code?

for(int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
 System.out.print(i + " ");
}

What is the output of this code?

int num = 85;
if(num >= 90)
 System.out.println("A");
else if(num >= 80)
 System.out.println("B");
else if(num >= 70)
 System.out.println("C");
else
 System.out.println("D");

What is the output of this code?

for(int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
 if(i == 2) {
 continue;
 }
 System.out.print(i + " ");
}

What is the output of this nested loop code?

outer: for(int i = 1; i <= 2; i++) {
 for(int j = 1; j <= 2; j++) {
 if(j == 2) break outer;
 System.out.print(i + "" + j + " ");
 }
}

What is the output of this code?

int count = 0;
while(count < 3) {
 System.out.print(count + " ");
 count++;
}

What is the output of this code?

int i = 0;
do {
 System.out.print(i + " ");
 i++;
} while(i < 0);

What will be printed?

char grade = 'B';
switch(grade) {
 case 'A': System.out.print("Excellent");
 case 'B': System.out.print("Good");
 case 'C': System.out.print("Average");
 default: System.out.print("Invalid");
}

What is the output?

int x = 5;
int y = 3;
if(x > 3)
 if(y > 4)
 System.out.println("A");
 else
 System.out.println("B");

What is the output?

for(int i = 10; i > 0; i -= 3) {
 System.out.print(i + " ");
}

What is the result of this expression?

int a = 10, b = 5;
int result = (a > b) ? (a < 20) ? a : b : 0;
System.out.println(result);
